ip|German torpedo boat|T13||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Type 37 torpedo boat]] was bombed and sunk by aircraft in the [[Kattegat]]. 20 crew were killed.<ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=6112434 |shipname=T13 |accessdate=20 July 2012}}</ref><ref name=GronerBd1/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-878||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type IX submarine|Type IXC/40]] [[submarine]] was [[depth charge]]d and sunk in the [[Bay of Biscay]] west of [[Saint-Nazaire]], [[Loire-Inf\u00e9rieure]], France ({{coord|47|35|N|10|33|W}}) by {{HMS|Tintagel Castle|K399|6}} and {{HMS|Vanquisher|D54|6}} (both {{navy|UK}}) with the loss of all 51 crew.<ref name=U878>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/boats/u878.htm |title=U-878 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=[[German cruiser Seydlitz|''Weser'']] \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The incomplete auxiliary [[aircraft carrier]], a former {{sclass-|Admiral Hipper|cruiser|2}}, was scuttled at Kiel. }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==11 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=11 April 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese net layer|Agata Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The auxiliary [[netlayer]] was sunk in the [[Andaman Sea]] east of [[Car Nicobar]]({{coord|08|55|N|98|38|E}}) by [[Consolidated B-24 Liberator]] aircraft of [[No. 203 Squadron RAF|203 Squadron]], [[Royal Air Force]].<ref name=\"Japanese Submarine Chasers\">{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/CH-7_t.htm |title=Japanese Submarine Chasers |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=11 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese submarine chaser|CH-7||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass2-|No.4|submarine chaser}} was sunk in the Andaman Sea east of Car Nicobar ({{coord|08|55|N|98|38|E}}) by Consolidated B-24 Liberator aircraft of 203