ehund]] midget submarine.<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Panama|1915|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship capsized and sank in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|44|30|N|33|30|W}} with the loss of 45 of her 50 crew.<ref name=Jordan446>{{cite book |title=The world's merchant fleets, 1939 |first=Roger |last=Jordan |publisher=Chatham publishing |location=London |year=1999 |page=446 |isbn=1 86176 023 X}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Port Wyndham||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy UC 63B]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the English Channel east of Dungeness by [[Seehund|''U-5070'']] ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Posen|1925|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[hospital ship]] was bombed and sunk by Soviet aircraft off Hela. 300 killed.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=5606273 |shipname=Posen |accessdate=27 October 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Ramona'' \n|flag={{flag|Sweden}}\n|desc=World War II: The fishing [[lugger]] was shelled and sunk in the [[Baltic Sea]] south of the [[Utklippan]] Lighthouse by {{ship|Soviet submarine|K-56||2}} ({{navy|Soviet Union|1935}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wlb-stuttgart.de/seekrieg/45-04.htm |title=Seekrieg 1945, April |accessdate=10 October 2015 |last=Rohwer |first=J\u00fcrgen |authorlink=J\u00fcrgen Rohwer |author2=Gerhard H\u00fcmmelchen |work=W\u00fcrttembergische Landesbibliothek Stuttgart |publisher= |language=German }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese minesweeper|Tamasono Maru No. 2 Go||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=The auxiliary minesweeper was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/japan/jap_esc_aux_ms.htm |title=Auxiliary Minesweepers of WW II, Japan |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=22 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Togo Maru|1923|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary minesweeper was torpedoed and sunk in the Pacific Ocean off the Japanese coast by {{USS|Parche|SS-384|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|TS-10||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The minesweeper was bombed and sunk by Soviet aircraft off Hela.<ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=6120343 |shipname=TS-10 |accessdate=4 August 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 1102||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The submarine chaser was bombed and sunk off Hela by Soviet aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref name=UJ>{{cite web |url=http://www.kbismarck.com/kriegsmarine-submarine-chasers.html |title=KRIEGSMARINE SUBMARINE CHASERS (Ubootj\u00e4ger) |publisher=KBismarck |accessdate=11 October 2015}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==12 April==\n::''For the severe damage to ''Sperrbrecher 185 Hans Burg'' on this date, see the entry for [[List of shipwrecks in September 1944#6 September|6 September 1944]].''\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=12 April 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Dione|1940|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: [[De Havilland Mosquito]] aircraft of [[No. 143 Squadron RAF|143]], [[No. 235 Squadron RAF|235]], [[No. 248 Squadron RAF|248]] and [[No. 333 Squadron RAF|333 Squadrons]], [[Royal Air Force]] bombed and sank the cargo ship at [[Porsgrunn]], Norway. Raised post-war, repaired and returned to service in April 1946.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref name=HomeD>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/homefleet/shipsd.html |title=Norwegian Homefleet&nbsp;\u2013 WW II, Ships starting with D |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=9 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 961||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germa