asers |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=19 April 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German guard ship|DB 06 Nanny||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The [[guard ship]] was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_conc_patrol.htm |title=Auxiliary Guard ships and Minesweepers of WWII, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=18 April 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Ekins|K552|6}} \n|flag={{navy|United Kingdom}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The {{sclass2-|Captain|frigate}} was severely damaged by a [[naval mine|mine]] in the [[North Sea]]. Declared a [[constructive total loss]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/5658.html |title=HMS Ekins (K 552) |author= |date= |work=Uboat.net |publisher= |accessdate=15 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 569||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The Type C2M minelaying ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mfp.htm |title=MFP landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|Laffey|DD-724|6}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Allen M. Sumner|destroyer}} was severely damaged off [[Okinawa]], Japan by a [[kamikaze]] attack with the loss of 32 of her crew. Repairs took until 6 September to complete.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M-368||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[M-class minesweeper (Germany)|M 1940-class]] [[minesweeper]] was sunk in a collision with a [[U-boat]] off [[Southern Norway]].<ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=6116018 |shipname=M-368 |accessdate=4 August 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese tanker|Shincho Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: Th