24532/http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1144 |archive-date=1 December 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==20 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=20 April 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Altengamme||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship was sunk in the [[Baltic Sea]] off [[Sa\u00dfnitz]], [[Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]] by [[Soviet union|Soviet]] aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Ethel Crawford'' \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The trawler struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Firth of Clyde]] ({{coord|55|13|N|5|14|W}}) with the loss of all ten crew.<ref name=EC>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3497.html |title=Ethel Crawford |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=9 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|K\u00f6nigsburg||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[coastal trading vessel|coaster]] was sunk in the Baltic Sea off [[Hel, Poland|Hela]], [[Reichsgau Danzig-West Prussia|Danzig-West Prussia]] by Soviet aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German trawler|V 215||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The ''[[Vorpostenboot]]'' was sunk in the Baltic Sea off Hela by Soviet aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194504/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==21 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=21 April 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minelayer|Ostmark||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The auxiliary [[minelayer]] was bombed and sunk by British aircraft west of [[Anholt (Denmark)|Anholt]], Denmark.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=5607487 |shipname=Ostmark |accessdate=27 October 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-636||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII 