.ru/ivs/bibl/paperno/for_65_engl.htm |title=The unknown World War II in the North Pacific |publisher=KSCnet |accessdate=26 April 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|SC-1019}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=The {{sclass-|SC-497|submarine chaser|2}} ran aground and sank in the [[Yucatan Channel]] ({{coord|22|28|N|84|30|W}}) north west of Arroyos de Mantua, Cuba.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/9035.html |title=SC-1019 of the US Navy |publisher=U Boat.net |accessdate=22 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Sverre Helmersen||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Liberty ship]] struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and was damaged in the [[North Sea]] off [[Ramsgate]], [[Kent]], United Kingdom by {{GS|U-2326||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). She was towed to [[Falmouth, Cornwall]], where she was declared a total loss. Scrapped in 1948.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref name=SH>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/singleships/sverrehelmersen.html |title=D/S Sverre Helmersen |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=8 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|Swallow|AM-65|6}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Auk|minesweeper}} was sunk in the Pacific Ocean off the [[Ryukyu Islands]], Japan ({{coord|26|10|N|127|12|E}}) by a kamikaze aircraft attack.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-518||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type IX submarine|Type IXC]] [[submarine]] was [[depth charge]]d and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] north of the [[Azores]], Portugal ({{coord|43|26|N|38|23|W}}) by {{USS|Carter|DE-112|6}} and {{USS|Neal A. Scott|DE-769|6}} (both {{navy|USA|1912}}) with the loss of all 56 crew. }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==23 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=23 April 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese guard boat|Aji Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=The auxiliary guard boa