telain|DE-149|6}}, {{USS|Flaherty|DE-135|6}}, {{USS|Hayter|DE-212|6}}, {{USS|Hubbard|DE-211|6}}, {{USS|Janssen|DE-396|6}}, {{USS|Keith|DE-241|6}}, {{USS|Neunzer|DE-150|6}}, {{USS|Pillsbury|DE-133|6}} and {{USS|Varian|DE-798|6}} (all {{navy|United States|1912}}) with the loss of 26 of her 59 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|UIT-2||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The submarine was scuttled at Genoa.<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|UIT-3||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The submarine was scuttled at Genoa.<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 206||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The submarine chaser, a former {{sclass-|Gabbiano|corvette}}, was scuttled at Venice. Raised, repaired and put in Italian service as ''Bombarda'' in 1951.<ref name=\"APE class submarine chasers\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_esc_ape.htm |title=APE class submarine chasers |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=14 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 2221||2}}, {{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 2222||2}}, {{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 2224||2}}, {{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 2227||2}}, and {{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 6083||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The submarine chasers, former {{sclass-|Gabbiano|corvette|2}}s, were scuttled at Genoa.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1226 |title=German Sub Chasers Captured Italian |publisher=WarshipsWW2 |accessdate=5 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808053133/http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1226 |archive-date=8 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 2225||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The 