ines |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=8 April 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Sheldrake|L06|6}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Kingfisher|sloop|1}} was damaged/sunk in the [[North Sea]] by a Kriegsmarine [[Seehund]] midget submarine.<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Takasago Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The tanker was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Gulf of Siam]] by {{HMS|Tradewind|P329|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Teisho Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary naval vessel was torpedoed and sunk in the Java Sea by {{USS|Gabilan|SS-252|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-286||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was [[depth charge]]d and sunk in the [[Barents Sea]] ({{coord|69|29|N|33|37|E}}) by {{HMS|Anguilla|K500|6}}, {{HMS|Cotton|K510|6}} and {{HMS|Loch Insh|K433|6}} (all {{navy|UK}}) with the loss of all 51 crew.<ref name=U286>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u286.htm |title=U-286 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=14 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-307||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was depth charged and sunk in the Barents Sea ({{coord|69|24|N|33|44|E}}) by {{HMS|Loch Insch|K433|6}} ({{navy|UK}}) with the loss of 37 of her 51 crew.<ref name=U307>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u307.html |title=U-307 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=15 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-1017||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC/41]] [[submarine]] was depth charged and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] north west of Ireland ({{coord|56|04|N|