rce.org |accessdate=4 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|LSM-12}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=The [[Landing Ship Medium|landing ship medium]] was wrecked and abandoned at Okinawa. Subsequently stripped for parts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/12597.html |title=LSM-12 of the US Navy |publisher=U Boat.net |accessdate=4 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|LST-675}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=The [[landing ship tank]] was wrecked and abandoned at Okinawa. Subsequently stripped for parts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/11735.html |title=LST-675 of the US Navy |publisher=U Boat.net |accessdate=5 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M-802||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[M-class minesweeper (Germany)|M 1943-class]] [[minesweeper]] was bombed and sunk by American aircraft at Kiel.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=6121705|shipname=M-802 |accessdate=16 October 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Mexphalte||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[tank ship|tanker]] was sunk in an American air raid on Kiel.<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese escort|Mokuto||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Ukuru|escort ship|1}} was [[naval mine|mined]] and sunk in the [[Shimonoseki Strait]] ({{coord|33|53|N|131|03|E}}). Twenty-seven crewmen were killed.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/Mokuto_t.htm |title=Japanese Escorts |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=4 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MS|Monte Olivia|1924|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[hospital ship]] was bombed and sunk at Kiel by American aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=5606342 |shipname=Monte Olivia |accessdate=27 October 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|New York|1926|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[ocean liner]] was bombed and sunk at Kiel by American aircraft. Wreck scrapped from 2 August 1949 at [[Dalmuir]], Scotland, and from January 1950 at [[Troon]], Scotland.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=5606668 |shipname=New York |accessdate=16 October 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|R-59||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[R boat|Type R-41 minesweeper]] was sunk at Kiel by American aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref name=\"Warshipsww2.Eu\">{{cite web |url=http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=762 |title=German coastal minesweeper Type R-41 |publisher=Warshipsww2.Eu |accessdate=2 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007024640/http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=762 |archive-date=7 October 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{Ship|German minesweeper|R 119||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The minesweeper was sunk in an American air raid on Kiel.<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|R-261||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[R boat|Type R-218 minesweeper]] was sunk at Kiel by American aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref name=\"ReferenceC\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese landing ship No. 145|T-145||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass2-|No.101|landing ship|2}} was seriously damaged running aground on Derikyonma-Zaki ({{coord|28|11|N|129|40|E}}). She was refloated on the 11th had to be abandoned as there was no hope for salvaging her.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/T.145_t.htm |title=T-145 |publisher=www.combinedfleet.com |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>