hips Taken To Sweden |day_of_week=Wednesday |date=11 April 1946 |page_number=4 |issue=50114 |column=E }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Samida||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy TBC 123]]: The [[Liberty ship]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[English Channel]] off [[Dungeness (headland)|Dungeness]], [[Kent]] by [[Seehund|''U-5363'']] ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref name=LibS>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/LibShipsS.html |title=Liberty Ships&nbsp;\u2013 S |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=6 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Saint Mihiel|1945|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy CU 65]]: The [[T2 tanker]] collided with {{SS|Nashbulk||2}} ({{flag|United States|1912}}) in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|37|44|N|64|40|W}}), caught fire and was abandoned.<ref name=CU65W>{{cite web|url=http://www.warsailors.com/convoys/cu65.html |title=Convoy CU 65 |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=12 June 2012}}</ref><ref name=Mihiel>{{cite web|url=http://www.usmm.org/natlantic.html |title=U.S. Ships Sunk, Damaged or Detained in North Atlantic During World War II |publisher=USMM.org |accessdate=12 June 2012}}</ref><ref name=T2QRS>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/T2Q.html |title=T2 TANKERS - Q - R - S |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-677||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was destroyed at [[Hamburg]] in a British air raid.<ref name=U677>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u677.htm |title=U-677 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=15 May 2016}}</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-747||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was badly damaged by bombs at [[Hamburg]] in an American air raid. She was scuttled on 3 May 1945.<r