marine|Shch-310||2}} ({{navy|Soviet Union|1935}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=5605904 |shipname=Ilmenau |accessdate=27 October 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|MTB 710}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Fairmile D motor torpedo boat]] was sunk by a [[naval mine|mine]] off [[Zadar|Zara]], [[Italy]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/17249.html |title=HMS MTB 710 of the Royal Navy |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=11 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Hosei Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[tank ship|oiler]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Sunda Strait]] ({{coord|05|25|S|106|39|E}}) by {{HNLMS|O 19}} ({{navy|Netherlands}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/Hosei_t.htm |title=Japanese Oilers |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=10 April 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M 504||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[minesweeper]] was sunk at Kiel in a British air raid.<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|HMS ML|102}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The motor launch was torpedoed and sunk in the [[English Channel]] off [[Dover]], [[Kent]] by a [[Kriegsmarine]] [[midget submarine]].<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Neuwerk|1912|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The refugee ship was torpedoed and sunk off the [[Hel Peninsula]], [[Reichsgau Danzig-West Prussia|Danzig-West Prussia]] by {{ship|German torpedo boat|S 708||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of about 960 lives. There were eight survivors.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=1132066 |shipname=Neuwerk |accessdate=27 July 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|R-69||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[R boat|Type