tor |accessdate=1 May 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Hagane Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] south of [[Honshu]] by {{USS|Sennet|SS-408|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Isuzu Maru No. 3||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary [[guard ship|guardboat]] was torpedoed and sunk in the Pacific Ocean south of Honshu by {{USS|Cero|SS-225|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese auxiliary gunboat|Kaiho Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: Convoy TSO-201: The auxiliary [[gunboat]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] off [[Hokkaido]] ({{coord|42|22|N|142|16|E}}) by {{USS|Sunfish|SS-281|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}). 5 crewmen are killed.<ref name=Sunfish/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/japan/jap_esc_aux_pg.htm |title=auxiliary gunboats of World War II |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=20 April 2015}}</ref><ref name=Kaiho/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Kairyu Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary gunboat was torpedoed and sunk in the Pacific Ocean south of Honshu by {{USS|Silversides|SS-236|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Kaiyo Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[coastal trading vessel|coaster]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Yellow Sea]] by {{USS|Trutta|SS-421|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Kinshu Maru'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The boat was sunk in the Yellow Sea by {{USS|Trutta|SS-421|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M-403||2}} \n|flag={{