ostenboot]]'' was sunk in the Baltic Sea off Hela by Soviet aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194504/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==21 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=21 April 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minelayer|Ostmark||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The auxiliary [[minelayer]] was bombed and sunk by British aircraft west of [[Anholt (Denmark)|Anholt]], Denmark.<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=5607487 |shipname=Ostmark |accessdate=27 October 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-636||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was [[depth charge]]d and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] west of Ireland ({{coord|55|50|N|10|31|W}}) by {{HMS|Bazely|K311|6}}, {{HMS|Bentinck|K314|6}} and {{HMS|Drury|K316|6}} (all {{navy|UK}}) with the loss of all 42 crew.<ref name=U636>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u636.htm |title=U-636 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==22 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=22 April 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Amiji Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[patrol boat]] was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] south of [[Honshu]] by {{USS|Cero|SS-225|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese guard boat|Ariake Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=The auxiliary guard boat was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/japan/jap_esc_aux_pc.htm |title=Auxiliary Patrol and guard boats, Japan |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=22 May 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Idefjord||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy PK 9]]: The [[tank ship|tanker]] was torpedoed and damaged in the [[Barents Sea]] ({{coord|69|40|N|33|14|E}}) by {{GS|U-997||2}}