7|S|112|52|E}}) by {{USS|Besugo|SS-321|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}) with the loss of 54 of her 55 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 2220 Lago Zuai||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[submarine chaser]] was scuttled on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_conc_patrol.htm |title=Auxiliary Guard ships and Minesweepers of WWII, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=12 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 2222||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The submarine chaser, a former {{sclass-|Gabbiano|corvette}}, was sunk off Genoa by United States Navy [[PT Boat]]s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1226 |title=German Sub Chasers Captured Italian |publisher=WarshipsWW2 |accessdate=6 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808053133/http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1226 |archive-date=8 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian submarine chaser|VAS 202||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|VAS 201|submarine chaser|2}} was scuttled at [[La Spezia]], [[Liguria]], Italy.<ref name=\"Warshipsww2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1278&tridit=lodenice&zobraz=A |title=Italian submarine chaser class VAS 201 |publisher=Warshipsww2 |accessdate=4 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140911065023/http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1278&tridit=lodenice&zobraz=A |archive-date=11 September 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==24 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=24 April 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian destroyer|Alpino|1938|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The {{sclass-|Soldati|destroyer}} was scuttled at [[Genoa]], Italy.<ref name=seekrieg194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|Frederick C. Davis|DE-136|6}} \n|flag={{navy|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Operation Teardrop]]: The {{sclass-|Edsall|destroyer escort}} was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] ({{coord|43|52|N|40|15|W}}) by {{GS|U-546||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 115 of her 209 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 617||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The Type C2 ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mfp.htm |title=MFP landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 0770||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The [[F-lighter|MZ-B landing craft]] was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"Navypedia\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mz.htm |title=MZ type small landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 819||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The Type DM minelaying ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mfp.htm |title=MFP landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 831||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The Type D ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk on this date. Salvaged in 1946 and put in Italian service as ''MZ 831''.<ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mfp.htm |title=MFP landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list ite