vy|UK}}) but was declared a [[constructive total loss]].<ref name=Redmill>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3505.html |title=HMS Redmill (K 554) |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=27 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|Sperrbrecher 167||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The ''[[Sperrbrecher]]'' struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[North Sea]] off [[Cuxhaven]], [[Schleswig-Holstein]] ({{coord|53|59.3|N|8|31.6|E|format=dms}}).<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=3007688|shipname=Sperrbrecher 167 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese submarine chaser|Yusen Maru No. 31 Go||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=The auxiliary [[submarine chaser]] was sunk on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/japan/jap_esc_aux_sc.htm |title=Auxiliary Sub Chasers of WWII, Converted Merchant Ships, Japan |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=22 May 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==28 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=28 April 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese submarine chaser|CH-17|1942|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The {{sclass2-|No.13|submarine chaser|2}} was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk off Tomei Harbor, Fukue Shima, [[Goto Archipelago]], ({{coord|32|25|N|128|46|E}}) by {{USS|Springer|SS-414|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/CH-17_t.htm |title=Japanese Submarine Chasers |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=29 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese cable layer|Hashima||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Hashima|cable layer|2}} was torpedoed and sunk off Kii Suido south south east of [[Mikizaki]] ({{coord|33|55|N|136|18|E}}) by {{USS|Sennet|SS-408|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.combinedfleet.