194504/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Miho Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: Convoy MOSI-05: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Yellow Sea]] by {{USS|Trepang|SS-412|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194504/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/Ojika_t.htm |title=Japanese Escorts |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=2 May 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese minelayer|Nuwajima||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Hirashima|minelayer}} (A.K.A. ''Nuwashima'') was bombed and damaged by [[Boeing B-29 Superfortress]] aircraft of the 314th Bomb Group. Her stern was hit and blown off and she was beached on Onyu Shima ({{coord|32|56|N|131|05|E}}). Fourteen crewmen were killed. Scrapped post-war.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/nuwajima_t.htm |title=Japanese minelayers |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=7 May 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian minesweeper RDV 127|RD 127||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The RD-class minesweeper was demolished by her crew at Monfalcone.<ref name=\"RD class minesweepers, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_mine_rd.htm |title= RD class minesweepers, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian minesweeper RDV 128|RD 128||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The incomplete RD-class minesweeper was demolished at Celli shipyard, Venice.<ref name=\"RD class minesweepers, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_mine_rd.htm |title= RD class minesweepers, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian minesweeper RDV 129|RD 129||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The incomplete RD-class minesweeper was demoli