il 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-3525||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type XXI submarine|Type XXI]] [[submarine]] was bombed and damaged in the western [[Baltic Sea]]. She was consequently scuttled at [[Kiel]], [[Schleswig-Holstein]] on 3 May.<ref name=U-3525>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/boats/u3525.htm |title=U-3525 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=30 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Yuna Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[tank ship|tanker]] struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Gulf of Siam]] off [[Lingga, Malaysia|Linga]], [[British Malaya|Malaya]].<ref name=seekrieg194504/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==Unknown date==\n::''For the sinking of the Belgian tanker ''Ampetco'' as a target during April 1945, see the entry for [[List of shipwrecks in September 1944#18 September|18 September 1944]].''\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=Unknown date 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German training ship|Adler||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[training ship]] was sunk by Allied bombers at [[Kiel]].<ref>\n{{cite web |url=http://www.navalhistory.dk/english/theships/p/pederskram%281908%29.htm |title=Peder Skram (1908-1943) |editor=Johnny E. Balsved |date=4 April 2005 |work=Naval History \u2013 Royal Danish Navy |accessdate=12 February 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120104232710/http://www.navalhistory.dk/english/TheShips/P/PederSkram(1908).htm |archive-date=4 January 2012 |url-status=dead }}\n</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese auxiliary submarine chaser|CHa-199||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[No.1-class auxiliary submarine chaser|''CHa-1''-class auxiliary submarine chaser]] was sunk off Matsure Light, Japan by a [[naval mine|mine]] sometime in April.<ref name=\"1-Go auxiliary submarine chasers\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\