y |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Rufleet\">{{cite web |url=http://wio.ru/fleet/sunk/baltic.htm |title=ships sunk in the Baltic by soviet aircraft |publisher=Rufleet |accessdate=3 May 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Hummel||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The cargo ship was wrecked at [[Stettin]], [[Pomerania]]. Wreck scuttled in 1947.<ref>{{csr |register=MSI |id=1095179 |shipname=Hummel |accessdate=25 November 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese depot ship|Kibitsu Maru||2}} \n|flag={{army|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Kibitsu Maru|depot ship}} sprang a major leak near [[Kobe]] and was beached to prevent sinking sometime in April. Refloated in April and was under repair from April\u2013July before returning to service.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/Kibitsu_t.htm |title=Japanese Army/Navy landing Craft Depot Ship |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=7 August 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German support ship|LAT 30 Prinses Beatrix||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The light gun carrier/landing fire support ship was sunk on 14 April, or sunk on 8 May by Soviet aircraft in the Baltic Sea.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://wio.ru/fleet/sunk/baltic.htm |title=Ships sunk by Soviet aircraft in the Baltic |publisher=Rufleet |accessdate=4 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_conc_lss2.htm|title=Auxiliary landing Fire Support ships of WWII, Converted Merchant Craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=4 May 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item \n|ship={{HMS|LCA 1346}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=The [[landing craft assault]] reported lost in the Mediterranean Sea during April.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.navypedia.org/ships/uk/brit_aws_lcalcsm.htm |title=LCA Assault Landing Craft and LCS(M) Support Landing Craft, Royal Navy |publisher=Navypedia |