rmany/ger_mine_rd.htm |title= RD class minesweepers, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian minesweeper RDV 140|RD 140||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The incomplete RD-class minesweeper was scuttled at Picchiotti shipyard, Limite Sal Arno in late April.<ref name=\"RD class minesweepers, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_mine_rd.htm |title= RD class minesweepers, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref>}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian minesweeper RDV 147|RD 147||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The incomplete RD-class minesweeper was scuttled at Castaguta shipyard, Genoa in late April.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_mine_rd.htm |title= RD class minesweepers, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=22 April 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian submarine chaser VAS 236|RA 261||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The ''VAS 231''-class [[submarine chaser]] was scuttled at [[La Spezia]], [[Liguria]], Italy sometime in April.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1279&tridit=lodenice&zobraz=A |title=Italian submarine chaser class VAS 231 |publisher=Warshipsww2 |accessdate=3 April 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140911065435/http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1279&tridit=lodenice&zobraz=A |archivedate=11 September 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German motor torpedo boat|SA 2||2}} and {{ship|German motor torpedo boat|SA 3||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The ''MS 11''-class [[MAS boat|MS boats]] were scuttled at La Spezia sometime in April.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=903&tridit=lodenice&zobraz=A |t