er head to the beach to find buried treasure. ||14 June 2007\n|-\n| 27 || 27 || Roary on Thin Ice || On a cold day at Silver Hatch race track, Roary must find a way to warm everyone up in time for an important race. ||21 June 2007 \n|-\n| 28 || 28 || Motormouth || A commentator (Murray Walker) is invited to report on a stunt display by the cars, but he has other ideas, and confesses he has always dreamed of racing himself. ||23 June 2007\n|-\n| 29 || 29 || Demolition Derby || Tin Top keeps crashing into things, and Big Chris tries to help him focus his energy into something productive. ||25 June 2007 \n|-\n| 30 || 30 || Manners, Please || Farmer Green and FB are nervous about going to Mama Mia's garden party, so James and the other cars teach them how to behave at the event. ||27 June 2007 \n|-\n| 31 || 31 || Crash Landing || Hellie has trouble getting airborne again after making an emergency landing. || 1 July 2007 \n|-\n| 32 || 32 || Plugga's New Job || James breaks down, causing Mamma Mia to ask Plugga to drive her around, but when the pair have fun together, the out-of-action chauffeur begins to get jealous. ||4 July 2007 \n|-\n| 33 || 33 || Silver Hatch Fun Run || Big Chris is undecided about taking part in a fun run, so Roary and Plugga try to make sure he trains for it without realising. ||5 July 2007 \n|-\n| 34 || 34 || Silver Hatch Heroes || A film director visits Silver Hatch to record his new movie. ||6 July 2007 \n|-\n|}\n\n===Season 2 (2008)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Overall !! Episode !! Title !! Description !! Airdate\n|-\n| 35 || 01 || Nick Solves the Case || Nick solves the case of the missing biofuel. ||10 July 2007\n|-\n| 36 || 02 || Drifter's Last Day || The little car worries that Dragga is to be taken to the scrapheap! ||11 July 2007\n|-\n| 37 || 03 || Out of Juice || Big Chris takes delivery of special rainwater to make the cars run more smoothly. ||12 July 2007\n|-\n| 38 || 04 || Roary's Wake Up Call || Farmer Green has problems getting up in the morning, so Roary finds a way to help. ||14 July 2007\n|-\n| 39 || 05 || Big Chris Says Sorry || Big Chris thinks Marsha is cross with him after he corrects a mistake made by Mrs. Carburettor. ||17 July 2007\n|-\n| 40 || 06 || Maxi's New Engine || Maxi's engine needs to be rebuilt. ||19 July 2007\n|-\n| 41 || 07 || A Busy Day for Big Chris || Big Chris struggles to find time to relax, because every time he sits down, someone at Silver Hatch race track wants his help. ||20 July 2007\n|-\n| 42 || 08 || Tin Top Gets Scared || Flash the rabbit decides to play a mischievous trick on Tin Top. ||21 July 2007\n|-\n| 43 || 09 || Roary Loses A Friend || Big Chris accidentally throws away Roary's lucky teddy, and sets out to retrieve it before it reaches the rubbish dump. ||22 July 2007\n|-\n| 44 || 10 || Spooky Forest || Maxi tricks the friends into thinking the forest is haunted. ||24 July 2007\n|-\n| 45 || 11 || FB in the Fast Lane || FB the flatbed truck competes against Maxi at the racetrack - with disastrous results! ||25 July 2007\n|-\n| 46 || 12 || Roary Goes Back to School || Roary heads back to school to brush up on his safety skills. ||26 July 2007\n|-\n| 47 || 13 || The Rabbit That Yelled Stop || Flash challenges Roary to take part in a race. ||28 July 2007\n|-\n| 48 || 14 || Cici Gets Fired Up || Silver Hatch suffers a fuel crisis, so everyone relies on solar-powered Cici! ||29 July 2007\n|-\n| 49 || 15 || Stars 'n' Cars || Big Chris is invited to sing karaoke on TV. ||30 July 2007\n|-\n| 50 || 16 || Crash Test Roary || Roary is nervous about racing after crashing into a tree while racing against Maxi. ||31 July 2007\n|-\n| 51 || 17 || Roary Sees Red || Cici gets stuck in the mud during a rainstorm while helping Farmer Green and FB with their annual hay harvest. ||1 September 2007\n|-\n| 52 || 18 || Rusty Takes a Trip || The cheerful racing car and his friends plan a surprise for Rusty. ||3 September 2007\n|-\n| 53 || 19 || Roary Cleans Up His Act || 