 Kong First Division League|Hong Kong First Division]]: [[2010\u201311 Hong Kong First Division League|2010\u201311]], [[2011\u201312 Hong Kong First Division League|2011\u201312]], [[2013\u201314 Hong Kong First Division League|2013\u201314]]\n*[[Hong Kong Senior Challenge Shield|Hong Kong Senior Shield]]: [[2016\u201317 Hong Kong Senior Challenge Shield|2016\u201317]], [[2018\u201319 Hong Kong Senior Challenge Shield|2018\u201319]]\n*[[Hong Kong FA Cup]]: [[2011\u201312 Hong Kong FA Cup|2011\u201312]], [[2012\u201313 Hong Kong FA Cup|2012\u201313]], [[2014\u201315 Hong Kong FA Cup|2014\u201315]], [[2016\u201317 Hong Kong FA Cup|2016\u201317]], [[2017\u201318 Hong Kong FA Cup|2017\u201318]], [[2018-19 Hong Kong FA Cup|2018\u201319]]\n*[[Sapling Cup|Hong Kong Sapling Cup]]: [[2017\u201318 Sapling Cup|2017\u201318]]\n*[[Hong Kong League Cup]]: [[2011\u201312 Hong Kong League Cup|2011\u201312]], [[2014\u201315 Hong Kong League Cup|2014\u201315]], [[2015\u201316 Hong Kong League Cup|2015\u201316]]\n\n===Individual===\n*[[Hong Kong Top Footballer Awards#Footballer of the Year|Hong Kong Footballer of the Year]]: 2014<ref name=POTY/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|69051}}\n\n{{Lee Man FC squad}}\n{{Hong Kong Footballer of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Recio, Fernando}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Spanish emigrants to Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Barcelona]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong footballers]]\n[[Category:Catalan footballers]]\n[[Category:Naturalized footballers of Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Association football utility players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Divisiones Regionales de F\u00fatbol players]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong First Division League players]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Kitchee SC players]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong Rangers FC players]]\n[[Category:Lee Man FC players]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong international footballers]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2018 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Asian Games competitors for Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Hong Kong]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=May 2014}}\n{{Spanish name|first=Recio|second=Com\u00ed}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Fernando Recio\n| image = Fernando Recio.JPG\n| image_size = 280\n| caption = Recio in action for [[Kitchee SC|Kitchee]] in 2012\n| fullname = Fernando Recio Com\u00ed\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1982|12|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Barcelona]], Spain\n| height = 1.84 m\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre-back]]\n| currentclub = [[Lee Man FC|Lee Man]] \n| clubnumber = 2\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 2003\u20132006 | clubs1 = [[UE Rapitenca|Rapitenca]] | caps1 = | goals1 = \n| years2 = 2006\u20132009 | clubs2 = [[CF Amposta|Amposta]] | caps2 = | goals2 = \n| years3 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs3 = [[CD Tortosa|Tortosa]] | caps3 = 31 | goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2010\u20132019 | clubs4 = [[Kitchee SC|Kitchee]] | caps4 = 98 | goals4 = 4\n| years5 = 2016\u20132017 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Hong Kong Rangers FC|Rangers]] (loan) | caps5 = 14 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2019\u2013 | clubs6 = [[Lee Man FC|Lee Man]] | caps6 = 5 | goals6 = 1\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 2017\u2013 | nationalteam1 = [[Hong Kong national football team|Hong Kong]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| club-update = 18 February 2020\n| nationalteam-update = 18:46, 14 November 2017 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Fernando Recio Com\u00ed''' ({{zh|t=\u5217\u65af\u5967}}; born 17 December 1982), is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays mainly as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]] for [[Hong Kong Premier League]] club [[Lee Man FC|Lee Man]].\n\nHe spent most of his professional career with [[Kitchee SC|Kitchee]] in Hong Kong after signing in 2010, eventually going on to represent the [[Hong Kong national football team|Hong Kong national team]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]], Recio only played amateur football in his country, representing [[UE Rapitenca]], [[CF Amposta]] and [[CD Tortosa]]. In June 2010 he was signed by [[Kitchee SC]] in Hong Kong, reuniting with former teammate \u2013 at both clubs \u2013 [[Ubay Luzardo]] (also a stopper). The club's manager, compatriot [[Josep Gombau]], had tried to acquire the player in the previous [[transfer window]], but failed.<ref name=\"TKP\">[http://www.goalgoalgoal.com/thread-288941-1-1.html \"\u5091\u5fd7\u7c3d\u65b0\u63f4\u7d44\u5f8c\u9632\u300c\u96d9\u5854\u300d\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002120304/http://www.goalgoalgoal.com/thread-288941-1-1.html|date=2 October 2017}}; [[Ta Kung Pao]], 5 June 2010 (in Chinese)</ref>\n\nOn 17 October 2013, general manager [[Ken Ng]] announced that Recio had renewed his contract until 2016. On 29 May of the following year he won the Hong Kong Player of the Year Award for [[2013\u201314 Hong Kong First Division League|2013\u201314 season]], receiving a [[Hong Kong dollar|HK$]]35,000 prize.<ref name=POTY>{{cite news|url=http://football.on.cc/cnt/news/newc/20140530/fbnewc0124x0.html|script-title=zh:\u5217\u65af\u5967\u81ba\u8db3\u7403\u5148\u751f|trans-title=|publisher=[[Oriental Daily News]]|language=Chinese|date=30 May 2014|accessdate=30 May 2014}}</ref>\n\nFollowing Kitchee's victory in the [[2018\u201319 Hong Kong FA Cup]], it was announced that Recio would leave the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hk01.com/%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82%E9%AB%94%E8%82%B2/333169/%E8%B6%B3%E7%B8%BD%E7%9B%83-%E5%88%97%E6%96%AF%E5%A5%A7%E4%BD%90%E8%BF%AA%E7%B5%90%E6%9D%9F9%E5%B9%B4%E5%82%91%E5%BF%97%E7%94%9F%E6%B6%AF-%E6%9E%97%E6%9F%B1%E6%A9%9F%E6%8C%87%E6%96%B0%E6%9D%B1%E5%AE%B6%E9%87%8E%E5%BF%83%E5%A4%A7|title=\u5217\u65af\u5967\u4f50\u8fea\u7d50\u675f9\u5e74\u5091\u5fd7\u751f\u6daf\u3000\u6797\u67f1\u6a5f\u6307\u65b0\u6771\u5bb6\u91ce\u5fc3\u5927|trans-title=|publisher=HK01|first=Chi Ho|last=Yuen|language=Chinese|date=25 May 2019|accessdate=1 June 2019}}</ref> On 19 July 2019, the 36-year-old signed for [[Lee Man FC]] of the same country and league.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.mingpao.com/ins/%E9%AB%94%E8%82%B2/article/20190719/s00006/1563528319904/%E3%80%90%E6%B8%AF%E8%B6%85%E3%80%91%E7%90%86%E6%96%87%E6%96%B0%E5%AD%A3%E6%B7%BB%E8%80%81%E5%B0%87%E5%A2%9E%E7%B6%93%E9%A9%97-%E6%9D%8E%E5%BA%B7%E5%BB%89%E8%88%87%E9%99%B3%E6%9B%89%E6%98%8E%E9%87%8D%E9%80%A2%E5%90%88%E4%BD%9C|title=\u7406\u6587\u65b0\u5b63\u6dfb\u8001\u5c07\u589e\u7d93\u9a57 \u674e\u5eb7\u5ec9\u8207\u9673\u66c9\u660e\u91cd\u9022\u5408\u4f5c|trans-title=|publisher=[[Ming Pao]]|language=Chinese|date=19 July 2019|accessdate=28 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nRecio received his [[Chinese nationality law#Hong Kong|Hong Kong passport]] in October 2017, at the age of 34, alongside compatriots [[Dani Cancela]] and [[Jordi Tarr\u00e9s (footballer)|Jordi Tarr\u00e9s]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.scmp.com/sport/hong-kong/article/2113730/spanish-born-jorge-tarres-condemns-violence-catalonia-he-eyes-hong|title=Spanish-born Jorge Tarres condemns violence in Catalonia as he eyes Hong Kong debut in Asian Cup qualifier|publisher=[[South China Morning Post]]|date=2 October 2017|accessdate=9 October 2017}}</ref> He made his debut for [[Hong Kong national football team|the national team]] on 5 October, in a 4\u20130 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] win over [[Laos national football team|Laos]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hkfa.com/news_details2/15258|title=International Friendly Match \u2013 Hong Kong 4:0 Laos|publisher=[[Hong Kong Football Association]]|date=5 October 2017|accessdate=9 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n=